+## Refined relationship-model context boundaries
+
+The implementation sequence further separates:
+
+- **Identity and Profiles** — Person identity, Topic Pack assignments, field values, provenance, profile templates, and purpose-readiness inputs;
+- **Organizations and Groups** — Organizations, Groups, Households, Memberships, departments, locations, and hierarchy;
+- **Relationships** — relationship edges, intent, boundaries, and optional manual assessment snapshots;
+- **Interactions and Commitments** — timeline facts, communications, tasks, promises, reminders, and next steps;
+- **Events and Calendar** — events, attendance, recurrence, and event-specific readiness;
+- **Knowledge and Resources** — notes, files, URLs, backlinks, and safe metadata;
+- **Review and Attention** — cadence evaluation, reason-only queues, optional Review Priority, readiness, sessions, snoozes, and explanation generation;
+- **Customization** — Topic Pack definitions, field schemas, layouts, saved views, policy definitions, and plugin contributions.
+
+No interface, connector, or plugin may calculate relationship status or Review Priority independently from Review and Attention application services.
